physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Ultrasound examination revealed generalized skin edema, bilateral pleural effusions, and peritoneal effusions in the fetus. Normal Doppler, normal placenta, and normal amniotic fluid were noted, without structural anomalies or signs of fetal anemia.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The current pregnancy at 22 weeks showed findings of fetal hydrops, while a previous pregnancy at 20 weeks displayed nonimmune fetal hydrops.
